).

(Based on photographs of the holotype and all examined specimens) Body brown to dark brown (brown-black in a few); legs and antennae brown; pronotum slightly darker than rest (Fig. 
16A, B
). Integument matt, with yellow pubescence.

Female.
Body color like male. Apex of abdominal ventrite V slightly sinuate (Fig. 
26G
). Proximal sclerites of bursa copulatrix elongate-kidney shaped, apex acute (Fig. 
16H
), base with slight concavity: each with 13-15 large spines mainly on the convex mesal edge, 10-12 smaller spines on disc.
